In [113]:

In [125]:
num_states = len(unemp_results.columns) - 1  # Subtract 1 to exclude 'District Of Columbia'
num_rows = (num_states - 1) // 5 + 1
fig, axs = plt.subplots(num_rows, 5, figsize=(30, 6 * num_rows), sharex=True)
axs = axs.flatten()

i = 0

for state in unemp_results.columns:
    if state == 'District Of Columbia':
        continue
    state_part = state if state != 'District of Columbia' else 'District Of Columbia'
    if state_part not in part_state.columns or state not in unemp_results.columns:
        continue
    ax2 = axs[i].twinx()
    unemp_results.query('index >= 2020 and index < 2022')[state].plot(ax=axs[i], label='Unemployment')
    part_state.query('index >= 2020 and index < 2022')[state_part].plot(ax=ax2, label='Participation', color=color_pal[1])
    ax2.grid(False)
    axs[i].set_title(state)
    i += 1

# Hide any remaining empty subplots
for j in range(i, len(axs)):
    axs[j].axis('off')

plt.tight_layout()
